                  recovery is successful to accuracy œµ that is
                  exponentially small in ‚Ñì, which is the case for
                  perturbations of local commuting projector codes,
                  our bound reads kd2D‚àí1‚â§O(n(logn)2DD‚àí1) for codes on
                  D-dimensional lattices of Euclidean metric. We also
                  find that the code distance of any local approximate
                  code cannot exceed O(‚Ñìn(D‚àí1)/D) if Œ¥‚â§O(‚Ñìn‚àí1/D). As a
                  corollary of our formulation of correctability in
                  terms of logical operator avoidance, we show that
                  the code distance d and the size d~ of a minimal
                  region that can support all approximate logical
                  operators satisfies d~d1D‚àí1‚â§O(n‚ÑìDD‚àí1), where the
